SwampCroc: {
	// DisplayName: Crocolog
	// Entry: These sneaky reptiles have evolved to mimic the logs sometimes found floating in their swamp. Their skin is like sandpaper, but the sand part is small blades instead.
}

GiantEel: {
	// DisplayName: Mammoth Moss-Eel
	// Entry: What happens when you combine large, territorial and overgrown? This! It is extremely aggressive and unbelievably strong. It's best to walk- well, run away. It doesn't like getting wet.
}

// GiantEelBody.DisplayName: "{$GiantEel.DisplayName}"
// GiantEelTail.DisplayName: "{$GiantEel.DisplayName}"

DragonFly: {
	// DisplayName: Dragonfollow
	// Entry: The nature of the Swamp made the Dragonfollow evolve in a particular manner. Its job is to bring up prey for the Mammoth Moss-Eel to eat, and then the Dragonfollow can enjoy the scraps.
}

Mudsquit: {
	// DisplayName: Mudsquit
	// Entry: A simple, classic, home- grown fish-that-explodes- when-full. That's right! If it has even the barest taste of your blood, it will explode violently. Why? Well, it explodes its friends too! Hope that helps.
}

// CryoStalker.DisplayName: Cryo Stalker
// FallenShaman.DisplayName: Fallen Shaman
// Shambling.DisplayName: Shambling

Mossmother: {
	// DisplayName: Younger Caracarcoss
	// Entry: A relatively young - but strong - apex predator of the mossy, spore-fueled Swamp. The larger, older Caracarcosses have never been seen...or have been for only a short time.
}

Mossling: {
	// DisplayName: Mossling
	// Entry: A small, docile, delicious morsel. Grows into the larger {$Mossmother.DisplayName} over years and years...if they're lucky. Very, very few are lucky.
}

NostalgicShard: {
	// DisplayName: Nostalgic Shard
	// Entry: An odd, half-dimensional creature that cannot stand people. It's said make to make people reminisce in a way that is uncomfortable, somehow. It is only visible with the Crystal Visors.
}
